nt, and diaspora. He presents them as examples of the visual culture of enslavement and critical to conceptualizing Black Atlantic art history. Ultimately, Rarey looks to the archives of transatlantic slavery, which were meant to erase Black life, for objects like the mandingas that were created to protect it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican diaspora. 0aAmuletsxHistoryzAfrica. 0aAmuletszAfricaxHistory. 0aArt objects, AfricanxHistory. 0aBlack peoplexMaterial culturezAtlantic Ocean Region. 0aCeremonial objectsxHistoryxSourceszAfrica. 0aCeremonial objectszAfricaxHistoryxSources. 0aMaterial culturexHistoryxSourceszAfrica. 0aMaterial culturexHistoryxSourceszAtlantic Ocean Region. 0aMaterial culturezAfricaxHistoryxSources. 0aMaterial culturezAtlantic Ocean RegionxHistoryxSources. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478024422?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478024422423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478024422/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131903-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_DUK_ALL